   p+3\right)}
\end{eqnarray} 
or, equivalently, as the sum of three generalized hypergeometric functions (corresponding
term by term to the series):
\begin{eqnarray} \label{hyperFd} 
&& {\cal F}^{{\rm MF}}_d(x) = \frac{1}{8} \pi ^{1-\frac{d}{2}} \bigg(\frac{2^{3-d} \csc \left(\frac{\pi  d}{4}\right)
