The expressions (\ref{serFd}) and (\ref{hyperFd}) are adequate for $d=1,3$. 
For $d=2,4$ one must first take the limit $d \to 2,4$ before evaluating. This is easy to do
with mathematica, and we give here only the two leading terms at small $x$:
\begin{eqnarray}
&&{\cal F}^{{\rm MF}}_2(x) = \frac{1}{4 \sqrt{\pi }}-\frac{x^2 (-4 \log (x)-3 \gamma_E +2+\log (16))}{16 \pi }+O\left(x^3\right) \\
