{\it Extension to LR elasticity}

We did not attempt to find expressions for the mean-shape in real space for LR elasticity in any $d$. In the most experimentally relevant case of $d=1$ however it takes a simple expression: integrating (\ref{SpatioTempLR}) from $t=0$ to $t= \infty$ leads
\begin{eqnarray}
{\cal F}^{{\rm MF , LR}}_{d=1} (x) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{\pi }}-x e^{x^2}  \text{erfc}(x) \ .
\end{eqnarray}
We note in particular the behavior around $x=0$, ${\cal F}^{{\rm MF , LR}}_{d=1} (x)  =_{x \ll 1}  \frac{1}{\sqrt{\pi }}- |x| +O(x^2)$, reminiscent of the $2/q^2$ tail in Fourier space. At large $x$, the mean-shape now decays algebraically as $ {\cal F}^{{\rm MF , LR}}_{d=1} (x) =_{x \gg 1}  \frac{1}{2 \sqrt{\pi} x^2} + O(1/x^4)$.

